# Scale & Spacing Tokens

All numeric foundations for the design system: raw scale, semantic spacing, component sizing, and utility tokens. All tokens on this page are **theme-agnostic** — they do not change between themes.

## Base Scale (`--scale-*`)

The base scale is a set of 45 CSS custom properties that serve as the numeric foundation for spacing, sizing, radius, and opacity tokens. All values are in `px`.

### Negative values

| Token | Value |
|-------|-------|
| `--scale-n16` | -16px |
| `--scale-n12` | -12px |
| `--scale-n8` | -8px |
| `--scale-n4` | -4px |
| `--scale-n2` | -2px |
| `--scale-n1` | -1px |

